FBIS3-47309 "dreas007_k_94005" FBIS-EAS-94-007 Document Type:Daily Report 11 Jan 1994 Laos President Receives New U.S. Ambassador BK1001094494 Vientiane KPL in English 0805 GMT 10 Jan 94 BK1001094494 Vientiane KPL Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Vientiane, January 10 (KPL) -- Nouhak Phoumsavan, president of the Lao People's Democratic Republic, on January 8, received Mr. Victor L. Tomseth who presented his credentials as ambassador extraordinary and plenipotentiary of the United States of America to Laos. The Lao president welcomed the U.S. ambassador and expressed hope that he would further make contribution to the gradual improvement of the relationship between Laos and the U.S.A. in connection with the humanitarian cooperation in excavating for the remains of the Americans missing in action during the war. The Lao president confirmed the Lao Government's constant policy to render cooperation according to its real capability and conditions. Concerning the narcotics issue, the Lao Government has exerted efforts and cooperated with international organisations in persuading mountainous people to eventually put an end to the poppy plantation and substitute it with crops and practise fixed highland farming. The U.S. ambassador expressed thanks to the Lao authorities and people for their humanitarian cooperation and pledged to do his best to fulfill his diplomatic duty. Mr. Victor L. Tomseth assumes the post to succeed Ambassador Charles B. Salmon Jr.
